doc.after: Fish found in Shoshone National Forest include at least six species and subspecies of trout including rainbow, brook and brown trout. The Yellowstone cutthroat trout is widespread throughout the Greater Yellowstone Ecosystem, but in the forest is mostly limited to the Shoshone River.[57][58] The mountain whitefish is also found in the Shoshone River, while the burbot is found in two streams in the southern regions of the forest.[57]
